list.name: Changes
list.comment: AdminMenu2 was created for choosing a zookeeper to change attribute to.AdminMenu3 was added to hcange the attribute of the zookeeper

task.summary: Different types of animal classes were created
Attributes such as canSwim and canFly were added to the classes.
A menu was added in order to interact with AnimalLexi. A few test animals were also added.
50 test animals were added to the code. Also, a function for displaying all the animals was added.
The sortAnimals function was created which can sort animals on lifetime from youngest to oldest. Also, the displayAnimals function got an input parameter.
In accordance with the teacher, new goals have been set. Therefore, the new class Zookeeper was created. Moreover, the attribute feedingtime was added to the animal class.
The attribute zookeeper was added to the animal class. 5 zookeepers was created.

Created a new function logInMenu. The attribute password was added to the Zookeeper class in order to log in to private menu. System exit was added for closing the program. DisplayAnimals function now only shows the current zookeepers animals.
New class AnimalDateTimePair for sorting animals by feedingtime that is based on today's date and time. The function showSchedule was created. Renaming of some functions.
In the Animal class new is-functions for sorting by category was added. Two methods AnimalCategoryMenu and sortAnimalsByCategory was added.

More robust error handling was added with the parseIntegerInput method. New zookeeper with no animals assigned was added to do negative tests. PerformConcert method was implemented which utilizes polymorphism.
In accordance with theacher, new goals were set. Admin class was created. New start menu was created for admins and zookeepers.
FindNameOrpassword method was changed so that both admins and zookeepers can use the method. Additionally, an admin menu was created.
AdminMenu2 was created for choosing a zookeeper to change attribute to.AdminMenu3 was added to hcange the attribute of the zookeeper
